Create virtual environment (make sure to be using python 3.5 or above in your virtualenv)

mkdir Catalog
cd Catalog
virtualenv env
source env/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt



Clone repository

git clone https://github.com/EDUlib/catalog.git


Run migrations

cd catalog
python manage.py migrate


Things to do

a) Edit settings.py with the right information
b) Edit my.cnf if using mysql database or delete if not required
c) python manage.py createsuperuser
d) populate table for organisations in admin after runserver


How to run

cd catalog
python manage.py runserver


Modules needed by virtualenv

django==1.11
requests
timestring
python-dateutil
